UID:10001000-1775158200-1775158200@townhallseattle.org
SUMMARY:J. Kenji López-Alt and Tessa Lark present Tasting Notes
DESCRIPTION:If nothing is truly new\, what is creativity? \nIn this special live event\, New York Times bestselling author and James Beard Award–winning chef J. Kenji López-Alt joins Grammy-nominated violinist and composer Tessa Lark for an evening of cooking\, music\, and conversation. Moderated by renowned food writer\, Serious Eats founder\, and Special Sauce host Ed Levine\, the program explores how creatives build on tradition\, transform influence\, and turn identity into expression. \nOn stage\, Kenji brings his signature curiosity to the kitchen\, while Lark\, a Kentucky-born musician who bridges bluegrass roots with classical virtuosity\, reveals how seemingly distant traditions can combine to form brand new sounds. Through live culinary demonstration and musical performance\, this special edition of Kenji’s Tasting Notes reflects on how cultures and ideas blend\, and how originality is less invention and more a reinterpretation of our shared cultural histories. \n\n					WHAT TO EXPECT Get ready for a multisensory experience that fuses live music\, cooking demos\, tastings\, and conversation. Think: A stunning Great Hall filled with the sound of Tessa Lark’s violin; curiosity-driven conversation guided by Ed Levine; and interactive\, culinary creativity with J. Kenji Alt-Lopez that is rumored to involve blindfolds\, nose plugs\, and…20 lbs. of gummy bears? You’ll have to join us to find out!
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/tasting-notes/
LOCATION:The Great Hall\, 1119 Eighth Avenue (enter on Eighth Avenue)\, Seattle\, 98101\, United States
CATEGORIES:Arts & Culture
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://townhallseattle.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/tasting-notes.jpg
END:VEVENT
